title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant Finn M24 Quite Rare
location: Aiken Williston Barnwell, Columbia, South Carolina
postcontent:
Mosin Nagant Model 24 Finn (made in Finland) is 8 on a scale of 10 in rarity.
Wonderful thing about Finn rifles is that they all were accurized at the factory when they were built.

This rifle is in fine condition, with matching bolt and receiver/barrel.  The action is smoother than most Mosins, and the bore has very strong rifling, frosted a bit.

The sling is brand new, old stock, that I bought directly from Finland.  This M24 will fill a hole in your collection for sure.  And, should you choose to shoot it, you will be amazed at its quality and accuracy.

Chambered for the cheapest high power cartridge, 7.62 X 54r, readily available.

postcontent:
For Sale: Russian SKS Tula 1952 ALL ORIGINAL, NOT a factory refurb. This is a collectors grade rifle. No re-arsenal markings or signs of refurbishment anywhere on this rifle. It has all matching numbers on the bolt, carrier, stock, receiver, receiver cover, magazine, trigger guard, rear sight, and gas tube. It has the original blade bayonet, original cleaning rod, original cleaning kit, 10 stripper clips, 200 rounds of Russian match grade 7.62x39 ammo, and case. The bore is bright and shiny with strong rifling. The bluing is original and none of the pats have been painted over later. The stock is its original dark hardwood finish and has the original serial number without being forced matched and having a bunch of XXXXX's over the old serial number. The stock has no cracks or deep gouges, just minor handling wear. The receiver cover is marked with the Tula star inside the star logo and has the date stamp of 1952r under the logo. I bought this gun over a year and a half ago and it has sat in the safe ever since. I have never fired it, and never planned to in order to keep it in the collectors condition it is currently in. I know what this gun is worth as would any serious SKS collector so please don't try to low ball me and compare this with the Yugo's and Norinco's out there. Take a look at gunbroker for similar condition rifles and you will see that there are few out there and are worth every bit of my asking price. 

Asking $675 obo and I am not looking to trade, only sell outright at this time. I am located in Dublin and if you want to buy this, you must be willing to meet me in this area. title: For Sale/Trade:  Tactical .22 your mother warned you abour
postcontent:
What started off as a bone stock SW MP 15-22 has become the coolest .22 AR I have ever seen. She is built to get looks and shoot straight all day long and does it very well. The coolness factor is just through the roof with the custom touches and I get asked about and complimented on it constantly. Plus since it’s a .22 it’s a great rifle if your friendly because you can pass it around the range and talk to people without burning a hole in your pocket with ammo. That being said a lot of .22s are finicky with ammo this one isn’t. I built it to shoot everything and I’ve got a very large mixed box of everything from super high velocity hollow points to the standard lead nose blazer ammo and I mix and mingle with no loss of accuracy or failure to feed.
Okay lets start from the back and work our way forward. She has a rubber shoulder pad not for recoil just for comfort and a full length sling mounted to the 6 position mil-spec collapsible stock. The grip isn’t stock and I forget who makes it magpul  I think sitting on a custom trigger in a custom painted lower receiver. I added red and white accents to make her stand out plus with the pain I added to the fire selector its not a lot easier to tell where it sits at a glance. I used automotive grade bright white and Viper red. The trigger has a 4lb spring it from JP and a gunsmith polished trigger effectively reducing the trigger weight by half. She is by no means a hair trigger so no accidental discharge but on a weapon this like those 3 lbs I shaved off greatly aid in accuracy.  
As we move forward we come to the fore grip with the remote pressure switch for the light which is fully functional on two modes, ON and STROBE. This light is a 240 lumen LED and she is blinding but still very light and out of the way. There is a red dot optic on top with 4 reticle choices and 0-7 brightness with zero being off. I was concerned about the red dot washing out the light was so bright but even on the brightest day outside there is no issue.  There is a full rail system on the weapon which is all polymer as is the stock so it’s a very light weapon. The flash suppressor isn’t stock, I had the factory bird cage removed and I have a demon glass breaker as well as a barrel shroud suppressor which will accompany the gun. 

I am also including the iron sights.
If I can’t find the factory trigger springs and grip I will either reduce the price to compensate for their absence or replace them at the buyer’s request.

The DOA 600 reticle is the scope's centerpiece, however, as it dramatically extends your effective range and helps you judge a buck's trophy quality in record time. Short for Dead On Accurate, DOA technology features Rack Bracket reference lines, which help you accurately gauge the size of whitetail and mule deer antlers at distances that are difficult for standard optics. Because these lines represent the distance between an average deer's ears, you'll know the approximate distance once the lines fit the image. It all adds up to drop-dead certainty and fewer excuses at the moment of truth. Offering aiming points from 100 to 600 yards in 100-yard increments, the DOA 600 is compatible with today's most popular deer-hunting bullet/load combinations

title: For Sale:  HK P2000 V2 | 9MM w/3 Straps
location: 1367 Velp Ave Green Bay, Wisconsin, United States
postcontent:
The first of the many recent additions to the Heckler & Koch handgun line, the P2000 and incorporate features of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with the latest innovations of HK engineers. A refinement of a design created for several European police agencies, the P2000 is available with a traditional double-action/single-action trigger mode and the LEM/CDA (Law Enforcement Modification, also known as Combat Defense Action) trigger system first introduced in 2001 on the USP Compact "LEM" model.
The HK Law Enforcement Modification trigger system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull from first to last round fired) with a double-action hammer system.
Developed especially for a U.S. government agency, the Law Enforcement Modification (or LEM for short), is a unique trigger mechanism created specifically to improve the trigger performance and reduce the weight of the Double-Action Only (DAO) trigger pull on HK pistols.
With this mechanism, HK pistols can be fired like a standard DAO semi-automatic pistol where every round is fired by simply pulling the trigger fully rearward with the hammer starting at the forward rest position. The design of the proprietary HK LEM system allows the weight of the DAO trigger pull to be reduced to a smooth and constant 6.18 - 8.5 pounds (27.5 - 37.8 N) because the two-part hammer is pre-cocked every time the slide moves rearward. Trigger pull on conventional double action pistols is 12 - 15 pounds (53.4 - 66.7N).
The unique LEM pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. Optional adjustment (by HK certified armorer) can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.
Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation — one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the P2000. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single action pistol.
A set of simple-to-install modular grip panels allow the P2000 to be custom-fitted to any shooter’s hand. An ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers make handling the P2000 natural and easy for right and left-handed shooters alike.
Industry standard mounting rails allow the widest variety of lights, laser aimers, and accessories to be added to the P2000 by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 includes the same recurved, hook trigger guard found on the USP Compact and uses reliable and widely available USP Compact magazines.

title: For Sale:  WWI Steyr M1912 1914 9mm SemiAuto Pistol 97% Bluing Machined Steel! Orig Cond
postcontent: WWI Steyr M1912 1914 9mm SemiAuto Pistol 97% Bluing Machined Steel! Orig Cond (+ one box ammo-45 count). Here is an excellent example of the Steyr M1912 (dated 1914) 9mm semi automatic pistol. This pistol has a non-removable magazine (like the broomhandle mauser) and fires the 9mm Steyr ammunition fed by stripper clips. The condition is excellent with an area of thin shallow rust mottling (tattooing) but only on the left side (see photos). The barrel is immaculate with sharp clean rifling. The face of the breach show very few shells ever were fired. The top of the magazine well and follower are bright and shiny as well the trigger, hammer, and barrel! The wood grips have sharp cut cross hatching and appear as new. Outstanding opportunity to acquire such a fine example! The small letter proofs found on the Steyr-Hahn are the last initial of the person inspecting the part. The most common inspection stamp is the letter "K", the proof of Meister Josef Kogler. This sale includes one box of ammo (count 45-someone shot 5 rounds).
